                    <span>This book is wonderful and touching. The story is so sweet and sensitive, very thoughful. I would love to see a sequel...</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Destined to become a classic!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>5</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>12</span>
                      /
                      <span>12</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-11-24</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I love this little book. Personally, I think it's one of the best picture books to come along in ages! A girl finds a red book in a snowdrift. Inside are pictures of a boy on a tropical island. The boy is also reading a red book. Curious. His red picture book shows a girl in the city who is reading a book about a boy on an island... hey, woah! Lehman's illustrations beautifully convey the unique twist of this magical story/brain teaser for the very young (and not so very young.) The story is an inspiring message about the power of books transcending time and space to bring people together. For me, the best part about The Red Book is that it's a book within a book. The reader is not simply an observer, but a participant of sorts (since they're reading The Red Book too!)  I predict The Red Book becomes a classic.</span>
                  
              
